          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Membership_AddNewUser",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to add a new user to the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Membership.EC3Membership",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table in a SQL Server database. It checks if a user with the given email already exists in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Users",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. If the user exists, it inserts a new record into the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "EC3Membership",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table with a unique "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "AuthenticatedUserID",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and other user details. The procedure returns the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "AuthenticatedUserID",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " if the insertion is successful, otherwise, it returns 0."
        }
      ]
